      <text class="text-lg">
        <p>
          My name is Nhan Luong, but most people call me Len! I graduated from Monash University with an Honours degree in Computer Science. I am currently a research assistant and teaching assistant at VinUniversity. My current work is broadly in the realm of <b>AI4Science</b>.
        </p>
        <p class="py-2">
          I am passionate about teaching and inspiring new generation of scientists and engineers by cultivating their love for science and technology. I am also an aspiring computational scientist with a research interest that lies in the intersection of computer science, astronomy, and (astro)physics. Within the field of computer science, my primary interests are within <b>visual computing</b> (computational imaging, computer vision, computer graphics, visualization) as well as <b>data-intensive science</b> (numerical methods, simulation, data processing, machine learning, deep learning). I'm also passionate about teaching and inspiring new generation of scientists and engineers by cultivating their love for science and technology.
        </p>
        <p class="py-2">
          Outside of research, I enjoy reading and learning about sciences, philosophy, and visual arts. I'm a hobbyist photographer, with a particular interest in still life, pets, and street photography. I have two cats, Cam and Chanh, and you can find them <u><a href="https://www.instagram.com/cameowra.roll/">here</a></u>.
